Linux-Setns version 0.01
========================

setns is used to change the current namespace of the process by specifying a file descriptor to a currently available namespace.

So you mus provide a file descriptor and a type (CLONE_ALL, CLONE_NEWIPC, CLONE_NEWNET and CLONE_NEWUTS).

On successfull execution your process is now in a changed namespace.
In case of failure, error is returneCLONE_NEWIPC, CLONE_NEWNET and CLONE_NEWUTS).

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module does not require any 3rd party libraries, but it does require your machine to have the <sched.h> for build.

